devdoc.details: The Service Registry contract has an array of token address, and provides of service providers for tokens, this simplifies the creation of an ecosystems of service providers.

addCategory(bytes32,string).details: This method is only callable by the contract's owner

params._description: Description of the new service category
params._name: Name of the new service category

addService(address,bytes32,address).details: This method is only callable by the contract's owner

params._category: Name of the category the service belongs to
params._service: Address of the service to use
params._token: Address of the token that will use the service

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

replaceService(address,bytes32,address,a.details: This method is only callable by the contract's owner

params._category: Name of the category the service belongs to
params._newService: New address for the service to use
params._token: Address of the token that will use the service

transferOwnership(uint256).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

devdoc.details: The SnowflakeOwnable contract has an owner EIN, and provides basic authorization control functions, not based on an address as it is usual, but based on an EIN. This simplifies the implementation of "user permissions" when using Snowflakes.

constructor.details: The Ownable constructor sets the original `owner` of the contract to the sender account.

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

transferOwnership(uint256).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.
